  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops in London?",
  "response": "London is home to a vibrant coffee scene with numerous notable coffee shops. Here are some highly recommended ones:\n\n1. **Monmouth Coffee Company**: Renowned for its high-quality beans and expertly brewed coffee, Monmouth has multiple locations across the city. The Covent Garden shop is particularly popular.\n\n2. **Kaffeine**: With locations in Fitzrovia, Kaffeine is a favorite for its consistent high standards in both coffee and food. The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming.\n\n3. **Flat White**: Located in Soho, Flat White is celebrated for its Antipodean-style coffee and laid-back vibe.\n\n4. **Ozone Coffee Roasters**: Situated in Shoreditch, Ozone offers a great selection of single-origin coffees and a delicious brunch menu.\n\n5. **Prufrock Coffee**: A go-to spot for coffee enthusiasts, Prufrock in Farringdon is run by globally recognized barista champions and offers excellent coffee training courses.\n\n6. **Workshop Coffee**: Known for its specialty coffee and minimalist design, Workshop Coffee has several locations, with the Fitzrovia shop being highly rated.\n\n7. **The Attendant**: Housed in an old Victorian toilet in Fitzrovia, The Attendant is unique in both ambiance and excellent coffee.\n\n8. **Dose**: Located near St. Paul's Cathedral, Dose serves up quality coffee in a small, cozy setting.\n\n9. **The Gentlemen Baristas**: With multiple locations, this coffee shop blends Victorian charm with modern coffee brewing techniques and serves up excellent coffee.\n\n10. **Caravan**: Located in King's Cross (and other locations), Caravan offers exceptional coffee and a great selection of food in a spacious and airy environment.\n\nThese coffee shops represent just a few of the best spots in London for great coffee and unique atmospheres.",
